WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:52.700 --> 00:01:12.700
In a mixing bowl add mashed potato, fried
onion, fried red chili, coriander powder, garam masala powder and salt.

00:01:34.500 --> 00:02:14.500
 Mix them well.

00:02:14.500 --> 00:02:19.500
Our potato mixture is ready.

00:02:20.900 --> 00:02:29.900
Now take a small portion out of it in your
palm and press it flat.

00:02:29.900 --> 00:02:46.740
take one egg halves in the center and cover
with potato mixture. if it needs little more

00:02:46.880 --> 00:03:47.400
mixture to cover then add and make a fine
ball. It should look like an oval shaped "chop".

00:03:47.780 --> 00:03:53.100
 Set aside on a plate or refrigerate for 10 minutes

00:03:53.420 --> 00:04:53.480
Repeat this step to make 6 chops.

00:04:53.660 --> 00:04:57.500
All eggs are ready for deep frying. Beat an egg and keep aside.

00:04:57.500 --> 00:05:11.280
Heat enough oil in a pan. 

00:05:11.300 --> 00:05:29.700
Dip each chop in the beaten egg and coat with oat flakes.

00:05:29.700 --> 00:05:57.600
Place chops in the hot oil one by one.

00:05:57.960 --> 00:06:28.540
When one side is done turn other side. Fry them until golden brown.

00:06:28.780 --> 00:06:43.160
You can also use bread crumb instead of oat flakes for coating the egg chop.

00:07:06.200 --> 00:07:31.980
Egg chops are ready. Take out from the heat and keep them on paper towel to drain off excess oil. 

00:07:32.370 --> 00:07:42.930
Serve with tomato and mustard sauce.

